source.Name: Total population
source.Summary: Population: Total population and distribution by age and sex estimated to be consistent with the population by age and sex of the (a) 1963, 1974, 1985, 2004, 2015 censuses; (b) adjusted for under/over count; (c) adjusted for age heaping; (d) adjusted for under enumeration of children under age 15; (e) official estimates through 2024; (f) only total population for 1947, 2021 censuses; and with estimates of the subsequent trends in fertility, mortality and international migration. In addition, the (a) population register through 2017; (b) 2000, 2005-2006, 2010, 2017 MICS and 2008, 2013, 2019 DHS and 2016 MIS survey estimates have been considered.

source.Name: Life expectancy at birth
source.Summary: Overall Mortality: Life expectancy at birth and age pattern of mortality based on: estimates using LogQuad model life tables and estimates of under-five mortality (5q0), and adult mortality (45q15). In addition, the (a) registered deaths by age and sex available through 2015; (b) adjusted for underreporting of infant and child deaths; (c) adult deaths adjusted for underregistration using death distribution methods; (d) mortality rates for older ages were adjusted have been considered. Mortality rates for Spectrum were calculated by removing AIM's estimates of HIV-related mortality from all-cause mortality rate estimates published in the 2024 revision of the World Population Prospects.

source.Name: Age Mortality
source.Summary: Adult and Old Age Mortality: Estimates derived from: (a) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 2004 Census and 2016-2023 SRS; (b) recent household deaths adjusted at adult ages for underregistration using death distribution methods; (c) siblings deaths from the 2005-2006 MICS; (d) maternal orphanhood from the 1973 Pilot Census and 1974, 1985, 2004, 2015 censuses and 2000, 2005-2006, 2010, 2017 MICS and 2007 CWIQ and 2008, 2013, 2019 DHS; (e) paternal orphanhood from the 1974, 1985, 2004, 2015 censuses and 2000, 2005-2006, 2010, 2017 MICS and 2007 CWIQ and 2008, 2013, 2019 DHS; (f) intercensal survivorship from successive census age distributions; (g) estimates of under-five, adult and old age mortality. In addition, the (a) deaths by age and sex available from VR through 2015; (b) adjusted for underregistration; (c) recent household deaths data by age and sex from the 2015 Census; (d) siblings deaths from the 2008, 2013, 2019 DHS; (e) paternal orphanhood from the 1973 Pilot Census have been considered.

source.Name: Infant/child mortality
source.Summary: Child Mortality: Under-five mortality based on: (a) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2013, 2019 DHS; (b) indirect estimates from data on children ever born and surviving from the 1973 Pilot Census and 1974, 1985, 2004, 2015 censuses and 1992 DSMS and 2000, 2005-2006, 2010 MICS and 2016 MIS; (c) recent household deaths from the 1977 Survey and 1992 DSMS and 2004 Census; (d) International estimates used up to 2021. In addition, the (a) registered infant and child deaths through 2024; (b) direct estimates from births and deaths under-five calculated from full birth histories data from the 2008 DHS and 2017 MICS; (c) recent household deaths from the 2015 Census and 2016-2024 SRS have been considered.

source.Name: International migration
source.Summary: Migration: International migration based on: (a) information on foreign-born populations from censuses and registers from major countries of destination; (b) estimates derived as the differences between overall population growth and natural increase; (c) UNHCR statistics on the number of refugees in the main countries of asylum.
